Midgaard's academic interest in the Verdant Depths centers on the ruins in Zone 2: the single eye motif on the well capstone matches the Watchers' Cairn fragments found during Midgaard's foundation repairs, establishing a connection between the pre-civilizational peoples who marked Midgaard's site and those who built the forest ruins. Midgaard scholars are divided on whether this indicates a single pre-civilizational culture spanning the continent or parallel development of a common symbolic vocabulary; the Granite Arcade holds both the Watchers' Cairn fragments and the expedition rubbings from the forest ruins for comparative study. Midgaard's Containment Office holds intelligence on the Withered Depths' blight expansion and its relationship to the Verdant Depths' ecological resistance; the current assessment is that the Verdant Depths' defensive response is holding the boundary stable but not reversing the blight. Herbalists in Midgaard's market district pay premium prices for deep-forest preparations — medicines derived from plants that grow only in the Verdant Depths' outer zones. Supply has been declining for years as the Withered Depths' blight encroaches on harvesting zones.

